## Local Infrastructure
 
### What Runs Locally (Mac mini)
| Service | Port | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| PostgreSQL | 5432 | Conversation history + user profile |
| Qdrant | 6333 | Vector store for document embeddings |
| Chainlit App | 8000 | Web UI |
 
### What Runs in the Cloud (APIs)
| Service | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Anthropic API | Claude LLM inference |
| LangSmith | Observability and tracing |
 
### Hardware (Mac mini M4)
The entire local stack uses ~2GB RAM. A Mac mini M4 with 24GB RAM and 512GB storage is the recommended setup — it runs all Docker services locally during MVP development and is future-proofed for running local models later.
 
